# Auto-ship — commit, push, deploy (default)

Unless the user explicitly says **local only**, **no commit**, **no push**, or **no deploy** — finish substantive work by shipping it.

## Default end-of-task pipeline

After validated code changes (syntax check / lints on touched files):

1. **Commit** on `main` with a concise message focused on *why*.
2. **Push** to `origin/main` (`git push origin main`).
3. **Deploy** IAM Worker + dashboard: `npm run deploy:full` from repo root `/Users/samprimeaux/inneranimalmedia`.

Do **not** leave completed work uncommitted or unpushed unless the user asked to hold it locally.

## Opt-out phrases (honor immediately)

- "don't commit" / "local only" / "no push" / "no deploy" / "draft only"
- "plan only" / "review only" / "question only"

When opted out: summarize what would have shipped and list uncommitted files.

## Multi-repo (iam-pty)

If changes touch `/Users/samprimeaux/iam-pty`, commit + push that repo too. iam-pty is **not** covered by `npm run deploy:full` — restart/redeploy iam-pty separately when PTY server code changed.

## Git safety (unchanged)

- Never force-push `main`.
- Never skip hooks unless user requests.
- Never commit secrets (`.env`, raw tokens).
- Never amend pushed commits unless user explicitly requests amend.

## Deploy validation (not health-only)

After `deploy:full`, confirm Worker `/health` **and** dashboard asset URLs return 200. Failed chunk 404 → `npm run deploy:frontend` then re-check.

## D1 session sync (after commit/deploy)

Append one line to active sprint `agentsam_plans.session_notes` and upsert `agentsam_memory` project row when deploy succeeds (see `agentsam-d1-cursor-session-sync.mdc`).
